<item>
            <title>[LU-2392] Kerberos support (GSS keyring) is broken due to major structural changes between 2.6.x and 2.6.32</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-2392</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Kerberos support for lustre employs the GSS framework and the keyring mechanism (gss_keyring.c) to maintain and cache cryptographic keys in the Kernel. Due to major structural changes between 2.6.x and 2.6.32 the support is broken.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment>Linux distributions running Kernel &amp;gt;= 2.6.32</environment>
